text: This place is a bit hidden, but it's in the same center as WahlBurger.  We missed it my first time trying to find it, but after doing better research, found it on our 2nd day in Vegas. We came on a Sunday afternoon for lunch, and there were only 2 people in front of me, but it took a while to get my food (hubby went to try something else as he wasn't in the mood for hotdogs).   It started out as one person taking orders, making food, etc, so it took a while for me to actually get my food.  Hubby came back to order food from here too after browsing around, but I told him to go elsewhere b/c it was taking too long, and I'd already ordered. I got the dirty chilidog and dirty esquite (corn in a cup). The chili dog was amazing, and the bun was fantastic - crispy edges and perfectly buttered.  I had to save some for my husband to try since it was too good not to share.  The corn, absolutely delicious..... I can't wait to go back on future visits.

The hot dogs and fries were.amazing.  Try the fried Oreos too!  All very good!  The service was outstanding as well!  Devon and Flo were great!  I recommend this to anyone looking for a dive on the strip!
The k-town chicken wings were delish! I will definitely come back to try other dishes.

Absolutely delicious and priced reasonably. We got what was basically a chili dog with what tasted like Que Bueno inside. So so soooooooooo good and definitely reminded me of LA "street food" but more fulfilling. Also got the "dirty corn," which is covered in I think cottage cheese and cotija. 

We liked it so much that we actually went back right after inhaling the meal and got the exact same thing, plus some wings. Can't wait to check out the other Dirt Dog in LA.

Vacationing from out of town. Saw the reviews and gave it a try. Definitely the best hot dog I ever had ever. Had the mutt dog but liked the red side lot more. Will definitely try again if ever back in Vegas

Holy shit. Walking down the strip I had no idea this little hole in the wall food spot section existed. Best hot dog I've ever had. Just a tip, if you want a beer go into the T-shirt shop across from it, don't go to the bar next door, they overcharge. Next time im in Vegas I will def go here again.
Dogs are pretty good. Had the dirty chilly cheese dog. The best thing though was the deep fried Oreos.

So glad they brought this concept to Las Vegas! We visited their original location in Los Angeles and we felt in love with their food and service. The food here are as great as the one in LA plus they have chicken wings! Highly recommend their K-town and House Dog. The only down side is the small space and it's hidden in the back of Grand Bazaars Shop next to Sin City Bar and Wahburgers.
MmmMmmMmmmmmm...!!! My husband & I promised each other we'll eat here every time we come to Vegas. Lol SO GOOD!!!

UPDATE
Thank you Timothy for reaching out. I will revise again my review as soon as I get a chance to try your food.
Great hot dog joint! I forgot the name of the one I got but it was wrapped in bacon, smothered in fries, dressed with nacho cheese and a slightly spicy aiolii. Delectable.

Comprehension isn't possible for me when I'm hungry and it showed here when I was trying to figure out the menu.  Thankfully the staff here is awesome.  I had to get help from the staff and settled on the mutt dog which is a half green and half red dog.  I had a seat and within 5 minutes they brought me the awesome mutt dog.

This thing is awesome!  The red and green sauces both had a little bit of a kick to them.  They were delicious and I'd definitely come back to sample more of their menu.  My only regret in Vegas.  Even though this happened in Vegas, I'm not letting the secret stay there.  Go check it out

The place is so delicious! The hot dogs are reasonably priced compared to the other food items within the Grand Bazaar. It's located right next to Sin City Brewery and Fuel Bar, perfect for after a drink or FIVE.

The food quality is great for hot dogs, who would have thought? And the service is awesome. Open kitchen, you can watch everything they're doing so that's cool.

I can imagine be employees that work here eat all the time. And I'd definitely move to Vegas just so I can eat this almost everyday!

This place is really good and for the price no more then $7 per item? Shit! If your craving something good that wrap in bacon and top with that good good?  This place does not disappoint!!! Eli was awesome and I recommend coming here.
Good thing we tried this dog place called dirt Dog. If You ever here in Vegas Strip please try this place... Great staff also.
Absolutely the best ever! Will have to try all of the options thoroughly enjoyed the mutt dog.

Really good hot dogs.  Had the chili covered dog while the wife had the house dog.  Very good food. 
Pretty good price for the strip.  
Hidden in a corner of the Bazaar market in front of the Bally hotel.
Well worth trying.   
Bacon wrapped around a hot dog.  You can't go wrong with that.

On my last day in Vegas I thought this would be an amazing spot to stop by. Turns out, I was right! I got the multi dog without onions and no fries. I paid about $8 ish dollars for my meal. The hot dog was a decent sizing on this amazing bread bun with the proper amount of toppings. Very spicy and favorable. I ate pieces of fries from a friend's plate and they were quite tasty... but not tasty enough to pay $5 for them. 
For those of you with sensitive stomachs and hard heads, please eat at your own discretion. It's amazing for drunk food or a quick bite to eat. Be mindful that is could possibly give you gas if not more. Lbvs

I was really excited to try the hot dog! We had the house dirt dog and it was good but almost tooo drenched in sauce that it took away from the taste. The hot dog was also pretty burned on the bottom. I think I'll have to try it again some day and maybe have a better experience.

Tasted great. Very messy so be ready with mucho napkins.  There aren't many places to sit down and it is not the kind of thing you can walk and eat. Staff were awesome, ploite and welcoming. If you are on the fence they may give you a coupon to come back later.   Give it a try if you like funky food.
I had petty melt dog and it was delicious......! They have lots of choices. I went back to try another one. This one is The mutt dog and i have to say another over the top one. Must try.

Went here the other day for a quick bite. Been wanting to check out their LA location for a while now so I was pleasantly surprised to see that they opened a small stand type location here in Vegas. The menu offers unique hotdogs and sides. We opted for the Red Dog, the Mutt Dog, the Dirty Chili Cheese Dog, elote corn in a cup and chili cheese fries. The highlights were the Red Dog and the elote. The Red Dog ended up being my favorite because it had the most flavor and it was super tomatoey and spicy. The Mutt Dog to me was a brighter 
-milder version of the Red. The Chili Cheese Dog was good but lacked flavor compared to the other two. As for the sides, the elote was clearly better than the chili cheese fries. The place was busy and the food was made in a timely manor considering there were only too employees working in a little stall. The staff was friendly and accommodating. I will definitely come back the next time I'm in Vegas.

I got The Billionaire and some Asian themed dog- the name of which escapes me. The dogs and the toppings themselves were great, however it seemed like they used cheap store bought buns unbecoming of a dog at that price. 

Worth a try if you've never had foie gras on a hot dog, but they have room to improve - especially for the price.

So after walking all over the strip and walking by all the crowded and often over priced restaurants on the strip, we go searching for this hidden gem. I'm so glad we did because these hot dogs were incredible! I even got the elotes in a cup and that was amazing as well!  Health food this ain't!  But if you want a trip to flavor town, this is your ticket!!!  I definitely want to come back here next time in Vegas!
It was close to my hotel, so we went there twice. Hot dogs are taste good, and price reasonable. I love the cheese corn.

Delicious! Great combination of flavors. We were really surprise of how good they are. I'll recommend this place 100% you need to try it at least once. I had the house dog and fries. Also the price was good.

Saw the Los Angeles location on one of the many TV FOOD shows and had made a mental note to visit for my wife and the ELOTE DOG, Was walking by ... HEY ... I know this place!! So had to do it. The food is awesome, the staff were great. SO MUCH TO CHOOSE FROM!! The wife wanted the Elote and they had just started cooking it, they we so kind, they offered to bring all our food over to the little bar we were at before going to him. Food was great, service was great, can't wait to go back!!!

Tried the House Dog and the Elote Dog--both are packed with flavor and the bread they use for hot dogs are delicious! Also had the chili fries which were good and packed with chili without overpowering the fries.

I stopped by to eat at this place because I am a hotdog lover and it was super close to the hotel that I stayed. 

[Ambiance] A small place on the strip for to go/pick up orders. There are outdoor seatings outside if you choose to eat there.

[Food] I ordered the House Dog and the Red Dog. I thought I could eat two but they were actually quite bigger than I expected( I finished both of them anyway). The sausage was juicy and tasty but did not have the strong snap, if you know what I mean. They were very saucy, which you can already tell by the name of this place.

[Price&Service] The service was good. The workers were really friendly even when they were busy. I thought it was quite pricey but it was about average comparing to other restaurants around there.

There was only one guy working here at about 1:30 pm on a Thursday - he was doing everything, taking orders, ringing people up, doing the cooking and restocking ingredients, with many glove changes in between, so be prepared to wait. After waiting in line for about 20 mins to place an order (with only about 4 people in front of us), we waited next door at the bar for another 20 mins to get our food.  When our dogs finally were ready - they were delicious, but to think this might be a quick bite and you would be mistaken.  I have the original dog and my hubby had the mutt dog, he said his was very spicy.

I love the east coast hot dog buns we don't get here on the west coast. (nicely buttered and grilled)

The hot dog was delicious! Very flavorful and well done. I had the chili cheese dog, with fried Oreos for dessert. 
The service was quick and friendly. I would recommend if hungry for hotdogs.

This place was delicious!!!!! I will be coming back every time I visits Vegas 
The Elote fries where Fire !! I wish I would of taken a pic but I was to excited to eat

Loved it! I got the chili with the chili cheese fries! The place was small and does not have seating, but you can definitely order and they'll bring it to any location/restaurant in the shopping area.
Amazingggggg. I love it! Everything is full of flavors. I dont know if it's just me or the cheesy corn has the sweet after taste.
Go here, food is awesome!  Somewhat of a hole in the wall relative to the strip, but much better food than most of the "celebrity chef" restaurants
Amazing hotdogs and fries. They are super creative and tasty. Staff is super friendly and and build your hotdog as you would like too!!

Went to the little module strip mall on the LV strip. It was a neat little cluster of shops, bars and fast eats. It reminded me of shops in Mexico, just more modern and they had workers outside trying to lure you in by, offering deals and specials. There was music blasting. So it felt up beat and party like. We came across this hot dog stand that looked great, so we stopped to look at the menu. We only tried one thing and it was the Elote dog. Delicious! A grilled all beef dog, wrapped in bacon topped with a citrus, mayo based sauce, grilled corn, cotija cheese, bits of chorizo and cilantro on a soft, lobster roll like bun, that had been crisped up on the sides with butter. It was so satisfying! It had all the elements, that balanced out every bite and was just enough for a snack to share. It is outdoors and it was freezing that day. You have to find a spot to eat, which is bummer but the bars allow you to eat inside... if you buy a drink. This isn't the easiest to thing to eat and you are going to want to scoop up every, single, delicious bite. The service was good.  If you don't want to stand and wait, the workers will track you down in the strip mall and deliver your food to the shops or bars in the mini mall. This worked for us, since we decided to enjoy a beer at sin city brewery while we waited but please shoot them a tip! If you are in the area, you should test this out. Lots more on the menu that we will be back to try on our next visit.

Best hot dogs i had in my life!

Also surrounded by bars. You can go wrong with that!

Before you get lost using the yelp map- it's in the Grand Bazaar shops (next to CVS/ Bally's entrance behind Wahburgers. It's a tiny spot, there's some outdoor seating. The food was SO GOOD! Pricing was great for Vegas especially, like ~7 for a loaded hot dog. Green hot dog (chimichurri sauce) was my personal favorite. We got the elote, Buffalo wings, and three hot dogs. I got the "mutt" dog which was half red and half green - loved the green half so much I went back and got another one. The bread was buttery and perfect. Everything was great. The two guys working were super friendly, remembered our faces and brought us our food down the way. Highly recommend!

We ordered 3 house dogs and an elote dog along with dirty fries, elote fries and philthy fries. Everything was so amazingly good. Surpassed my expectations. We also ordered fries oreos and they gave us a free order. The horchata whip cream was great.

Recently went to the location at the Grand Bazaar Shops after reading a positive review in local publication praising the specialy bacon wrapped hotdogs. There were a few people when we got there on a Fri late afternoon . Location is quite small so basically order at the counter and find open seats at tables located nearby. My guest ordered the 'red dawg' and they asked/offered to make a combo for addt'l fee - which included fries and a beverage - Coke is a cold glass bottle (no fountain options available - so no cups with ice). They were told to take a seat and they're bring to table - they got theirs pretty quick - I ordered the 'dirty chili dawg' - and made mine a combo - asked what options besides Coke was told Gatorade so I had that (it was cold). I was too told to take a seat and food would be brought out. You have to pay on a tablet (no register) I was not provided option to give email for receipt (the young man doing the order taking didn't seem too interested in offering or was very personable for that matter )(was suprised on cc statement was charged about $15 for hot dog, fries & small bottle Gatorade). Anyways so my guest is about 1/2 way thru with their meal before I get my hot dog and they dont' bring the fries. I have to go back - try to get the guy's attention that took my order (he's in tunnel vision mode) to get my fries (read previous comments about the order taker) - had to wait close to 8 mins or so as they had to make a new batch (after getting attention of the lady that brought out my hot dog btw). The fries were very greasy and didnt' give good amount (since they were so greasy didn't mind). Anyways - I don't expect 5 star service at a place like this but it could have been better. Too many other options to get a decent meal than this - wasn't worth it. Wouldn't recommend.

Nice tiny little shop right behind Walhburger restaurant in the same aisle as Subway. I got their House dog, love their hot dog buns, way better than typical hot dog bun. so good! Will come back next time.
It was a little hard to find, it's right down the alley from the CVS. There is outdoor seating. The elote fries are amazing and the hotdogs are delicious. It is reasonably priced and pretty quick.

This place is so so good. I'm not even that big of a hot dog fan but this place knocked it out of the park. Bacon is wrapped around each hot dog and the buns have melted butter on them. So it just makes for an awesome hot dog. We got 3 hot dogs, 2 wings, and the fried Oreo and it was under $45. Dani, the lady who checked us out was super nice and helpful.
Holy moly! Flavor bomb in every bite. I had the Elote dog and it was amazing!!! I would recommend to everyone. Inexpensive and delicious - the perfect combo.

I had no idea this place existed but I saw a sign as I was walking past Wahlburger. 

I tried the chili cheese dog and the elote fries. I've never actually had elote but I didn't really like the fries. It had too much mayonnaise in it, but the quality of the fries themselves were good. I was starving but when I ordered both, I was feeling full before my food even came out. I knew it was going to be heavy and overwhelming, so I ended up throwing most of this away. It wasn't horrible though, but I would probably try something else next time.

Thankfully, the chili cheese dog wasn't too overwhelming. They use a buttered bread roll and it looks like it's a lobster roll basically, so that was really yummy. 

Overall, I think i'd definitely come back so I can try other things, but this has joined my list of must haves when visiting Vegas.

These guys got it right on unique spin on street food in Vegas!  Very creative hot dogs and I love how they use New England style hot dog buns just like how they would use it on Lobster Rolls!

Tried the Mutt Dogg (half green and red dog) and shared Elote fries.  Both were so amazing!  I definitely wanted to try a lot of their other items, but just did not have enough room! 

If you are close by and need something quick, definitely come here!
So bomb!!! Had their Cheeto elote and it hit the spot. Super fresh. Could use better sweeter corn but maybe it was just mine. Will come again.

UPDATE: so i was in my hotel room at Harrahs& decided i wanted dirt dog. i saw they closed at 2 & it was like 1:46 and i was on a mission ! i got there about 1:54 & they were still serving. i was quite impressed because usually people would say they were closed(i would) so i ordered something light because i wasn't sure if i would like it (something light being a bacon wrapped chilly cheese dog with bacon bits , cilantro and onions) . i told the guy how i liked my hot dogs (crispy) and he said no problem. fast forward to after i took the picture of my hot dog. i STILL wasn't sure if i would like it because i was wondering why the cheese was so light. i posted my pic and my phone died right after i wrote the review below. then i tried it ............. WOW ! i can't lie. that shit was GOOD ! pretty much, i'm going back today to try a different dog and some fried oreos. 




it's a little on the pricy side , but i'm sure it's due to location.... then again, they are gourmet hot dogs. they have hot dogs with fries on top, corn, avocado(you know everyone's crazy about avocados) , limes & they even have a bacon wrapped dog !!! who doesn't love bacon. 
they also have the mexican corn with cojita cheese and everything ! 
fries and wings as well. 
they do have fried oreos and twinkies but i haven't tried them yet but i will be soon.
The hotdog was okey. Inconvenient place to go eat. No parking. But their street corn was OUT of this WORLD!! Definitely coming back when I'm walking the area.
Great option for something less expensive on our trip on the strip.  We went here twice during our 5 day stay.

Well, now I understand what the problem was because the owner reached out to me and explained. I should actually know better because I was a chef for so long. 

Updating to 5 stars. 

I live closer to the South rainbow location, So, I showed Sean at the front and he took good care of me.

The hot dogs were all so good and everything was awesome. The wait was a bit but it's a really small location and they were pretty busy so it's expected. I felt like some hot wings so I ask the guys what's your hottest wings, I believe they only had 3 flavors. They tell me we'll are you really up for a challenge? Because we can make them as hot as your want. I was up for the challenge and said yea make me the hottest you can. Was I glad I did, they might have been some of the hottest but most delicious wings ever. All with a on the spot sauce. If you want some heat, don't hesitate to ask for something different. By the end of the night my mouth was on fire but I love heat so it was well worth it, by far hotter then BWW or Wingstop and 10x more flavorful. This place is awesome and the cooks and employees are really cool and friendly.

I got the "house dog" and my girlfriend had the "mutt" Both were excellent but both of us preferred the house dog over the mutt. The corn on the cob was also great, especially when you pair it with a glass Mexican Coca Cola. The manager was really friendly and even bought me a shot since it was my birthday.

Cool little street food spot tucked back in near Bally's. Some of the best Mexican street corn (dirty corn) I've had. They also had a hot dog of the same style called the dirty dog. Good for a quick bite.
The staff were super friendly and the hot dogs are to die for. Definitely will be back again next time. Only drawback is the location to me since it's a little cramped when busy.

I've been to Vegas a lot of times and this is the first time I heard about this place! it's perfect for an afternoon snack m. I ordered the Elote Dog and it was everything I imagined! Their fried Oreos were amazing as well!

We came here after discovering Pink's had moved and we still wanted hot dogs. We were greeted, ordered an elote dog and a a chili dog, and directed to sit at the tables and chairs under the pleasant cool mist dispensers. We were brought a free sample of fries while we waited. The owner (I think?) came out and was chatty and told us a little about the business' story, being inspired by the street food of LA. 

Our food came out, and it was initially wrong - 2 elote dogs - but the owner quickly brought us out the chili dog and let us keep the other elote dog. Great service! It was really filling and fancy (for hot dogs!) and worth the stop.

Stumbled on this place while searching on yelp for a quick bite for 6 people. We waited about 15-20 min for the food but we were kindly forewarned when we order as a big group had order right before us. The wait was definitely worth it. Everyone enjoyed their meal. 

My husband and I had the elote fries, dirty filthy fries, green dog and elote. We paid under $30 including tax and a tip, great value considering this is located on the strip. The fries are like a meal, not a side, and very filling. Every bite was delicious. 

This place also sells deep fried Oreos and Twinkies. I was too full after my meal to order more food but planning on going back!

This ain't your average Oscar Meyer Weinerschnitzel type hot dog joint!  This is some next level hot doggin' going on right here!  Their selection is solid and the sides are up to par too.  If I lived here I'd be back at least once a month to homage to best hot dog creations I've ever had.  Check it out if you get a chance.

It's 11:42 and this became one of my favorite hot dog joints a few weeks when I had visited the one on rainbow. But this spot on the strip was the opposite. They had no cheese no fries! I was really upset because my favorite dog was the patty melt. So I ended up ordering the red dog with the special cream cheese sauce which I did not get on my hot dog. Also wanted to order one of the specialty fries but couldn't because no cheese and no fries!.. this was really upsetting... the wings we orders was dryer than the desert in Las Vegas. I give 5 stars on the rainbow location but the one on the strip 2 stars....

From LA? At Staple Center?

Been there a few times never noticed them.

Back to the food...over priced low quality hot dog.  The toppings were good.  Cheapest food on the strip.

For Vegas it is ok.

Great balls of fire this place was amazing!!!

Me and my baby ordered the elotes cup...delish and two chili dogs. The chili dogs is what elevated me into heaven. There was a VIP party going on in my mouth. The flavors were coming from EVERYWHERE!

Let's start with that perfectly warm, buttered and crispy bun...that thing played A VITAL role in this mouth party. Then the chili was impeccably prepared. Not too sweet, or too salty...just pure perfection. As if this wasn't enough the actual bacon wrapped hot dog sent me over the edge. That thing had me ready to elope it at the little white wedding chapel it was so good to me. I told my boyfriend he had competition...as I had never felt a love quite like this.

It's been two days, and I can't get this thing outta my mind. Like, I'm about to buy a flight for this hot dog. Anyway, the experience was over just as quickly as it begin. I showed that dog no mercy as I inhaled it. This is a staple for me going forward. I would never visit the west coast and miss this dog.

Perfect "food truck" type food experience.  Everything on the menu is pretty cheap and good.  

My family of four ate like kings for $45.  Three "courses".  Fried twinkies and oreo were good for desert, and the cinnamon whipped cream to dip them in was to die for. 

Best thing on menu was the "elotes" fries with corn and lime and sauce and cheese on them.  If I was passing by and just wanted to share a quick nibble with a friend, maybe on my way to dinner elsewhere, that's what I would order.  I'd order that if walking by... even if I wasn't hungry.  They are that good.

We visited here while out walking around. There is one near us in Los Angeles and it has been on our to-do list. Let me start with the con of this place. I ordered the elote dog and the elote fries. After placing my order and paying, an employee came out to let me know that there was only enough corn for one dish or the other. I chose to have the elote dog and changed my fries to chili fries (which I didn't end up liking). The pro is that the elote dog was fantastic. I would like to check out the location in Los Angeles to have the elote fries. With all of this being said, if I had known prior to paying that they didn't have enough corn, I would have chosen to eat elsewhere. It was one of those moods where you're really craving a certain thing... And when that craving isn't satisfied you are left annoyed and disappointed. I will give them another shot.

Awesome hotdogs!!!! Highly recommend and gonna come back here every time I come back to Vegas! Elijah was great, friendly, and 5 star customer service. Quick and easy, and can't go wrong with the chili dog.

Dear Readers,

I just ate the best chili cheese dog ever. No cap. Like, I'm sitting here thinking about going for a second dog... i also had the elote fries which were good but in kind of upset that the flavor of the fries ( lime essence ) is overpowering the after taste chili dog.  

Seriously best chili cheese dog I've had in forever

The dogs and fries are really good here. I ordered one of the 2 top of the dogs, the dirty chili dog and one of the top fries, the dirty filthy fries. I'm not too much of a big fan of cheese sauce but it was good. Then Mix it with the chili, amazing! The dog itself was flavorful and the bun was good. The service was fast and friendly and very helpful in answering all of my questions on what to order. Can't wait to try more from the menu.
Zack and Justice were so friendly and had an awesome vibe while being patient and helping me and my aunt pick out what we wanted. Zack recommends the chili dog and it was AMAZING. Love this place
Hole in the wall place but perfect combination of flavors in each hot dog. Took it delivered to the nearby bar.

Visited this location several times during our trip. It's next to our hotel Planet Hollywood. It's pretty evident the guys working there enjoy what they do. The food is consistent with their customer service which is FANTASTIC! We had the Elote dog and corn cup as the side order- great eats for all of the walking on the Vegas strip. They use Nathan's all beef dogs and their buns are different & super yum! I think they are opening another place on the other side of the strip soon. Their original place is in California (LA). Reminds me of street food.

Tried to find this place of the yelp map. The location was off. Finally found it 1230 pm on a Friday . Not busy at all so I was disappointed when they messed up our order. We ordered 1 bacon wrap dog with mayo, mustard, ketchup , and onions. We also ordered 1 dirty corn. The dog came with mustard only. They left the corn out all together . I was hoping for a better experience .
Great food, matt gave great suggestions and wonderful hospitality. Not a long line and was greeted immediately. We got the house dog and my cousin got hers with chimichurri for an extra kick.

.... idk what to say... friendly staff, delicious street food, hotdogs wrapped in bacon?! I mean what more do you want? Filthy fries? They got that! Elote? Bruhhh you know they got that! One of my favorite dogs they have is the patty melt! Man! #FingerLickinDelicious #NotTheKFCSlogan This place is bomb dot com. You can not go wrong... especially with bars next to it!!! Best combo! Check it out... you wont be disappointed

Delish dogs located right outside the Linq. Perfect hangover food shared the "Green Dog" with my hub and it was delish.  Went Wednesday afternoon 9/20 and the young guy working was very friendly and welcoming. One suggestion...put some cilantro in your elote!! And some jalapeno! Would totally kick it up a notch. Otherwise, great place!

This location is garbage. Out of certain toppings for hotdogs, price is actually MORE than the rainbow location, the menu is smaller. Oh & cant forget about the managers shitty attitude. She tried to argue with me that the price was the same when if you go on the website the prices of these same items I got are cheaper. Then on top of that you gotta pay $9 for parking alonComing from a Vegas local, if you can go to the rainbow location. Much better!
really good hotdogs wrapped in bacon.  had the chilly dog was really good, one is enough for most people but 2 is better . the place is small and easy to miss. it is next to sin city brew.

Tried this place since it was right outside our hotel- being from San Diego means that I have a love for those LA street dogs. I came prepared to judge, but this place surpassed my expectations. These dogs are the best, we tried the house dog and the half and half dog. Along with the ktown wings and the elote fries I swear I've never had food like this. The chef is amazing and personally came out to hand us our food when the wait became a little too long for our last dog. The service is great, the food amazing - I'll definitely be driving up to LA to stop at their restaurant once I'm back home in SD. The chef said their next shop will be opening in Orange County but I'll keep my fingers crossed for a San Diego shop!!
The hotdogs were Great! Customer service at this location was good. The hotdogs were a little on the pricey side but worth it. I don't recommend the corn tho :(
The wings were very good and Contessa and Taylor were awesome definitely gave the place a good vibe

This place is AMAZING!

You'll be surprised how delicious these simple dogs are. I've been here several times and almost ordered everything on their menu; from the mutt dog, patty melt, all the way to their dessert side with the deep fried Oreos. Delicious. 

I would drink next door at The Fuel Bar and when I get my late night drunk snacking on. I'll swing on by here and usually order a dog or two hahha.

Their menu isn't really expensive for how great the food is and if you are a service member they do offer a discount for you! 

On the weekends be prepared to wait for a bit as they can get really busy with the orders. I wish I took photos of the food but I couldn't wait any longer to devour those dogs haha.
This place was amazing!!! Best hot dog EVER!!! Elijah was so personable which made it even better! We'll be back!

We reviewed on yelp before going and saw how good the reviews were.  We gave it a try and seriously!!  Our words were....."this is Bomb"!!  The buns are like crack.  So freakin good!!  I have had many hot dogs at many places, even the hot dog carts in Mexico and this is top notch!!  We will definitely be going back.  Highly recommended.  Service was very friendly as well.  Zero complaints on anything honestly, and I am highly critical.
OMG. Mutt Dog one of the best dogs I've ever had! Period. And the elote fries were delicious. Need a cheap, tasty lunch on the Vegas Strip? Beat a path to Dirt Dog.

Wowee! This is definitely not your Mama's hot dogs. These people know their stuff. They took ordinary dogs and thought up some gourmet creations with this cookout staple.

I ordered the hot dog with bacon and was blown away by the flavor combo.
It was bacony, cheesy, gooey goodness in a bun.
I also had the dirty fries and these were awesome. You may have dirty thoughts after these.
I saw that they also have deep fried Twinkies that I will try next time. I know that I will return.
I am sure that I will see you all there.

Happy yelping ya'll.

slightly better than my expectations. over priced. hot dogs came out cold when it's slow on a tuesday evening. the mayo is gross as hell. it's in a weird spot too. it's hard to find. if you see the subway keep walking go the end of the block and you'll see it.
Chili cheese and mutt dog was awesome!  Quick, reasonable, and convenient right next to a bar for some drinks to compliment the dogs.

We were randomly walking around and spotted this "hole in the wall" place! I'm a huge fan or corn and beef hotdogs. Everything on their menu sounded so delicious. We had the mutt dog, elote dog, dirty corn and fried Oreos. There was nothing left on our plates. The night before the place was sold out so we had to come back the last day of our stay. Once you order, you take a seat outside and they bring the food to you. Can't wait to come back again :)
I had the house dog packed with flavor was upset I finished it so fast because it was so good definitely coming back to try more

Dirt Dog was my favorite place to eat in all of Vegas! I had the Patty Melt and Red Dog along with some esquites, and it was all so delicious and flavorful. The price is perfect for a hearty meal to help start or end your Vegas day!

Ooh let me tell you this place is delicious! I broke my diet just for the hot dogs here! The sausage was good, the toppings makenit even better. Will stop by everytime i come to vegas. Must try at least once. Friendly service too

Cool hot dog place located in the bazaar of Bally's area.  They had some interesting flavor combos. I believe all the dogs are wrapped with bacon.  We tried the red dog,  which had a good spice kick to it and the party melt, which had melted cheddar fries on it. The dogs can be a bit messy, but its worth a try.

Amazing...how's that ?

So we found ourselves craving a hot dog in Vegas. We found this spot right outside our Ballys hotel. 

Atmosphere ??? It's vegas right on the strip. The prices, not bad. The service is friendly and the food is amazing. They have a great variety of hot dogs which are just tantalizing. We tried four different types and they were all fantastic. 

If your craving a hot dog don't hesitate and stop here.
Pattymeltdog And The Dirty Chili Fries Are Bombbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbb! Would Suggest

Taylor Joe and LALA really delivered this joint is everything you thought it would be the house dog amazing!!! The elote frys are not of this planet as a local we are always looking for little gems and in the heart of Las vegas they deliver our total ticket or $21.07 was more than worth every penny we reccomend this place to any tourist or local it is the real deal

This was easily the worst thing we ate on our week long trip to Vegas! I'm a huge fan of fried Oreos. But unfortunately, they retained the flavor of burnt old oil... very disappointed when I had to ask for my money back! 

The corn on a stick was inedible...but rather than walking back up for a second refund, I decided to dispose of it all.

I was shopping in the Grand Bazaar and as I walked by the Dirt Dog, I had to stop and take a second look. The menu was incredible! Teddy C. was the server and very helpful He explained what the different combinations were. These are not your average hot dogs! I had the Mutt Dog which is hotter on one end(red) and not quite as hot on the other (green). It was loaded with all kinds of toppings and definitely filled me up. This is the best of street food! Dirt Dog found unique and flavorful ways of serving up this American favorite.If you're on the strip and hungry for hot dogs, pass up the others and give Dirt Dog a try!
i got chili cheese fries and one of the dirty dogs!! it was rlly good! definitely over hyped but i wouldn't mind going again!
Nicest person I met in Vegas so far. Good food as well. We haven't had good luck with food so far and he said if we don't like it we can have another or a refund. Highly recommend this place.

Amazing hotdogs! Kenny catered to me and gave me the hot sauce that I asked for and then got his own stash and let me open his bottle which was so hot and just what I was looking for, also to finish it off with fried Oreos was sooo good! He also ran to the bar and got us all waters no problem and he also bought my dad a shot for his birthday. Never in my life have I had service like this. Highly recommend to anybody

THIS HOT DOG LITERALLY CHANGED MY ENTIRE LIFE. And the expert hit dog engineer was able to direct me to the perfect hotdog that would meet all of my needs - The Philly Melt. Ugh SOOO GOOD. I don't have words. The service was more than amazing, and the dog was the perfect snack. I'm going back for the desserts later

Delicious hot dogs and Elote(mexican corn on the cob). And pretty cheap for Vegas. It is a small shop, but the service is great. If you like hot dogs, you have to try Dirty Dogs. And if you are not sure which dog to try, ask. I wasn't sure about the house dog because the toppings didn't sound right. But I tried it anyway on recommendation of the cook and was really surprised at how delicious it was! Even the bun is better than any I have had before! Look forward to my next visit!
My boyfriend loved his hot dog! I came with him because the website said they have a veggie dog- unfortunately this location does not.
Amazing hot dogs . A must try for sure when you go to Las Vegas . It's in front of Bally's casino

Dog-gone-it! This stuff is delicious! Got the red dog and it hit the spot! Awesome beef frank with delicious grilled onions, drizzeld with red pepper flakes and spicy tomato type sauce chunk mixture. The heat is on! Corn elite with all the fixings= amazing! Get it! You won't regret it! ;-)

This was hands down the best hot dog I have ever had. 

So much flavor. First, butter buns and bacon wrapped dogs?!! Say no more. But then add the unique but simple toppings and you have something special. 

It's a small food stand type setup that's literally the size of a closet. The employees were full of energy and good vibes... dancing and singing and whipping up some delicious hot dogs to the music. I had to go back for seconds on my last day of the trip!

Highly recommend Dirt Dog while in LV.

One of my friends heard there was a Dirt Dog in Vegas and it was all he could suggest during our trip there. Finally after an extremely late night, promising him Dirt Dog was the only way we could get him out of bed and outside into the sunlight. He went directly for the Elote Dog and deep fried oreos. Honestly after the several years I've known him, I've never seen him this happy before.

I went with the Elote Dog and shared half of it with another friend who ordered the Dirty Chili Dog. I loved the chili on her hot dog, but I'll have to say the Elote Dog is pretty unique. The people working here were also amazing and we pretty much had a dance battle while they prepared our food. I wouldn't mind coming back here next time I need my hot dog fix in Vegas.
Food was great although we didn't know it was outside seating but it was worth it, definitely a hidden gem

I got the #DirtyChiliDog the first bite was outrageous. Loved this place from the start. Located at the Grand Bazaar shops out front of Bally's near the Las Vegas Strip. This place is a must try for tourists and locals. The bun is slightly toasted giving a unique flavor to the bread. The chili  is unreal and the cheese sauce drizzled with bacon bits and onion tastes amazing. Although there was not a whole lot of seating available the atmosphere surrounding the shops definitely draws you in. Glad I got a seat but if it were peak tourist season I could see many people wishing for a place to sit if you are in small groups you might have to share a table with strangers which is understandable and what I had to do. Taylor was very helpful and she knew the menu and made great suggestions pointing out several tasty items for a first time goer. Giving multiple options as a greeter is nice because it let me know "You can't go wrong." She made me feel excited to try something new which seems to come naturally to her she just has an inviting personality. I will definitely be back for more. I valeted at Bally's they charge $15 for the first 4 hours David and Jimmy were really nice at the Valet booth and Blue was my driver and he was very polite. I asked to tip the valet guys through the credit card payment option and the valet guys told me this was not possible unfortunately I did not have cash on me. It may be helpful to add a tip option so that I and others could generously tip those that make the service so wonderful.

The best hot dogs, corn and fries I have ever had! We found this place on Instagram and we are regular goers of Vegas so we had to go to this because it was the closest to us! This is a MUST in Vegas!

Quick version of review:
It was tasty! Had the elote dog. Worth trying.

More detailed version: 
$9 hot dog is pricey but it's gourmet I guess and on the strip, so the price reflects that. Bun was buttery and toasted, aka delicious. The elotes were flavorful and the dog as a whole was filling. I kind of viewed it as paying $9 for a premium hot dog with a side (the elotes) on top. 

My wait time wasn't bad at all, only had to wait 5 min (on a Monday early evening). People have mentioned the long wait, and I'd say if you see a long line might be worth revisiting at a more convenient time. 

Unclear why it's called Dirt Dog...

I give this place a thumbs up. Try for yourself, especially if there isn't much of a line.
The line wasn't too long and food was amazing! Loved the fries and dog! We tried 4 diff dogs and 2 diff fries and it all tasted great!

This is tge BEST dog Ice ever had!
We split the Dirty Chilidog and a order of Dirty Esquite. insane!
The chili is perfecttly flavor balanced and the esquite is elote in a cup with a twist. 
Come one come all, but you GOTTA come!

I had the elote fries and wow! The way the fries are seasoned and all the other ingredients just makes it a great combo! I loved the mix and also enough corn to eat a lone and taste like you are eating elote best of both worlds in one!
Had the elote dog - everything was so flavorful! The hot dog was perfectly cooked and the topping was spot on. A cute little spot tucked away just off the strip.

We stumbled on this street food stand in Las Vegas after walking all morning.  We didn't want a lot for lunch as we had reservations at a nice restaurant before a show that evening.  The prices were great and the food was amazing!  We split a dirty chile dog and cup of corn, and got beers from the place next door.  All in all a great, inexpensive and fun lunch!

Was craving hot dogs before EDC and lo and behold this little gem appears on our map right down the street. Its rare to find a legit hot dog place in most places I've been, but this one is it. The cashier was very friendly and recommended his favorite dog on their menu. I cannot remember the name but it was absolutely delicious. I'm confident their whole menu is of the same caliber. Highly recommend.

Probably my favorite place to eat on the strip. I work at Planet Hollywood and come here often. The manager is laid back and always makes sure every customer is happy. Definitely the best hot dog in Nevada.

For a tasty dog that is a meal in itself this is the place to go. But don't forget the dirty corn! Love it and will continue to order this as a side. We were too full for the sweet options but will be back later this week to try them. Don't give up if you don't see the sign immediately. They are on the street ( in the strip of little shops before escalators)before entering Bally's. Go to the last row of buildings beside Whalburger. It's a tiny place with outdoor seating. Well worth it.
We saw their video on facebook originally and had to go here because we love corn in a cup and were pleasantly surprised. Great service. Amazing food.  Elote dog is to dieee for.
Elote hot dog was the bomb.. place is a bit hidden but it's in the shopping center where whalaburger is located. definitely going back next time I'm in town

We got the House Dog and the Elote Fries at the recommendation of the staff - who were so nice and helpful. Really genuinely caring staff - Matthew went above and beyond to help us! Both dishes were delicious the House Dog sounds simple but the flavors are on point. A really good quick lunch spot, and we sat in Fuel Bar and they brought the food right over while we had drinks.

Dirt dog where do i start these boys are in the future. The food the vibe the setup it's all perfect. And their creativity is unprecedented. And they serve alcoholic really don't get no better then this.

This was a little hard to find, it's on the backside keep going until you see the wall burgers and make a right in the far right corner of wahlburger and the little shop is on the left. BY FAR THE GREATEST TASTING HOT DOG I HAVE EVER EATEN! I got the red tomatoe sauce hotdog wrapped in bacon. It was so spicy and good that my mouth was watering even after I ate two. One will fill up a girl, but for a guy that can eat I suggest at least two. They are about $7 each. Worth it.
Great dogs and fries! It was kinda hard to find, but well worth the search! We grabbed a beer next door and they delivered our food to our table quickly!

We personally feel like this is an under appreciated hidden gem!  Located right on the strip in the Grand Bazaar shops near Wahlburgers, its an inviting judgement free little spot with a dope setup, friendly staff and the "dirtiest" (tastiest) dogs and fries we've tried on this side of the map! We'll definitely come back!
Best hot dogs in Vegas...hands down.  This place is amazing, with very creative ways to make a hot dog.  Will definitely be going back to this place!!
This place has the most deicious hot dogs in the world in my opinion that is. Very tasty and delicious hot dogs. I think I should stop by again and get 5 more of these delicious hot dogs.
Absolutely delicious & the staff are extremely friendly! Highly recommend. I had the elote fries and they're mouthwatering.

I wish I can give it more than a 5 star for their delicious food and great costumer service. I had the ktown wings and green dog. The wings are the best wings I ever had...I'm not exaggerating. I wish I can describe the flavor but you must try it for yourself. The hot dog is so delicious that i would say is the best one I ever has as well. Better than any Sonoran dog I ever has that's for sure. I heard that they also have a location in downtown LA and I'm sure that I will visit them out there. Great food and amaizing costumer service at its best.

Amazing food. Great service. We found this on a website for food in Vegas. When we decided to come it was quite a walk but it did not disappoint. Great and very helpful employees. Once we ordered they brought our food to us and we weren't even sitting near the stand. About half way through the meal while we were enjoying our food, the manager himself came all the way to our table to see how our food was and if there was anything he could do to make our experience better. Being anywhere other than a fancy sit down restaurant in Vegas, you just don't get that kind of service.

Yummy elotes fries! With BACON!! 
Staff was so friendly and made sure we were pleased with our food. Definitely recommend.
Stopped by Dirt Dog on the strip for a quick bite to eat and Elijah hooked us up with some K-town wings.  They were awesome and we are definitely coming back for more.

Words cannot describe how amazing this place is. If you want phenomenal food with even better customer service, then definitely go here. 

The prices are some of the cheapest I've seen on the strip, and their food is like a gourmet version of awesome LA street food. 

Kenny really hooked us up with some of the best food I've ever had in Vegas. I can't wait to try the original restaurant in LA.

Great stop for the night! The location is in the Ballys strip which has many bars and great music. Outdoor seatings and fun environment no matter which place you end up choosing to indulge in. The food was tasteful and appealing. We wanted to try the fried twinkies and oreos but with our luck they were all sold out.
Best hot dog I've had. I got the street corn style fancy dog. I can't remember the actual name. It was great! I sat and had a beer next door at Sin City and it was prefect.

Fast, friendly service. Great prices on the strip. Fabulous food.
I was thinking about when I could go again two bites into my chili dog. Absolutely delicious. Best dog I've ever tasted.

Waited a long time to watch them make one, not the cleanest of facilities, not a bad dog inside the bun, had snap, but they drown it in all these toppings which is I guess their thing. Sorta pricey for a hot dog and yes its messy.

I saw a video of this place on Facebook and decided to  give it try! Dirt Dig is right next to Sin City Bar, tiny spot. The girls working at the time were friendly, helpful and fast! I ordered the green dog and Dirty corn to go, my order was ready in less than 10 mins. The hot dog is around $7 and totally worth it! I'll definitely come back !

This dog is the bomb! When you can get a Hot dog wrapped in bacon, sautéed onions house made chili Chipotle aioli extra bacon and melted cheese all on a toasted bun sprinkled with cojita cheese . Best dog ever! And the guys making them are awesome, friendly and professional. Go down the alley way and check this place out, you won't be sorry.

I liked this place. I enjoyed the corn my hotdog was spicy I didn't get what was recommended. So lesson learned . I enjoyed the number they gave for my order #7 which is my favorite number. But all in all it was a  Meh!

I had the elote hot dog and the elote fries and wow. It is definitely not for the faint of heart. The bun is a kind of garlic toast I believe. It's heavy but what else can you expect lol. I love that the food comes out super hot and everything is made to order. They have their Insider Food video playing on loop so it def amps up the hype.

Really, really, good dog that lived up to the hype.  I wish I remembered the girl's name who was there this day, but she was very prompt, cheerful, and happy to help and strike up conversation.   Will definitely be going when I'm back in town.
Been wanting to check this place out forever and I am so glad we did. We will be coming back for sure!
Dirt DOG! I really like this place. Overpriced and delicious hot dogs. Come here for the food not the service.

Service was much quicker than my first visit as they had more workers this time. Tried the RedDog and it had a nice spicy kick to it. Wish it was more spicy though but then again only freaks like me love the super spicy stuff. #besthotdogsonthestripuntilimprovenwrong

The food at Dirt Dog was so flavorful and satisfying. We had the chili dog and the esquite which had the perfect combination of flavors. Everyone was very friendly and attentive. We met Ken the owner who was very hospitable. He went out of his way to ensure we enjoyed our food bring us some jalapeños and the tasty fried Oreos with and horchata whipped cream. So delicious!!! Thank you Ken and you staff for such a great experience here in Vegas. We look forward to try the Los Angeles location. 

I highly recommend this place to anyone visiting Vegas.

Was so good we were back for dinner.

Went to Dirt Dog twice in my four nights in vegas --- and i'm thinking about going again tonight. 

The good: 
It was cheap, fast, and convenient. Has some outdoor seating nearby, whether its specifically for Dirt Dog I'm not 100% sure. 
The Hot Dogs were plump and juicy, the buttered bread was cripsy on the outside and soft on the inside. I had the spicy option on day one then last night I had the number one with the peppers and onions. 
Both were excellent although i'll give the nod to the spicy dog. 
Didn't try anything but the two dogs. 

The ok: 
Communication between staff was good on Tuesday, Wednesday needed some work. When i went on Tuesday there was no line so ordering was easy, pickup was easy etc. Wednesday night was a little different as there was several orders in front of me and it seemed like the staff had no clue who ordered what even though you provided them your first name for the order. There were more people working as well which could've added to the confusion as it such a small space. 

All in all I had a great experience. It's making me hungry just thinking about it... I may go back a third time before my flight home. If I'm back next year for our annual conference I'll definitely make my way over to try another option.

It's located right by the Sin City bar in the Bazaar Shops. Small walk up location with seating near by. 

So the prices are great for a budget! They aren't high at all! Then only two people working with a good size line they kept it fun and didn't seem they needed to rush in orders so they can get them all done. It was done within a timely manner.

I decided to go with the #EloteDog! OMG this dog is a burst of flavor at first bite. It was filled with fresh ingredients and she wasn't shy on the toppings either. Very filling in my opinion. 

I will be coming back with friends in the future!

The food here is unique and fulfilling. We ordered the patty melt dog (loved the chipotle aioli sauce), elote dog (never thought lime would go so well on a hot dog), and the dirty chili fries. My favorite thing would have to be the crisp lobster roll the dogs are served on. The prices are decent for street food as well. Hot dogs ~$7-8 and fries for a bit less.
Amazing place to get Hotdogs! Their Elote Dog tastes great. Definitely worth it. It was filling. Basically just like eating a burger. Customer service is great as well!
Omggggg the elote and hot dogs were amazing. I was seriously full for so long. I even had the fried Oreos. I will def be back to try something different. Everything was reasonably priced.

It was fine. I got the dirty esquite and all I could taste was chili powder. I also got a dirty chili dog that was over cooked, I had to cut the burnt part off then it was fine. The potential is there, but the execution when I went was poor and did not leave me wanting more. Probably won't try again.

Seen this places when i was walking around in Vegas on vaca and decided to try it out.The elote bacon wrapped hot dog was so good! I live in California so the good thing is that they have a Los Angeles location. Defiantly will be checking it out.

Dirt Dog has been on bookmark for quite some time, I found myself on the strip and decided to go for it and finally try it out. I got the Elote Dog. They use a lobster roll as a bun which was buttery and soft. The hot dog itself was plump and juicy and wrapped in a layer of perfectly cooked bacon. On top was the Elote mixture which was over stuffed(not like I'm complaining). They did give me a fork and knife but to really enjoy it, you have to just pick it up(even if the topping falls down, it like an extra treat once you finish the dog). It's not something you should eat everyday but boy was it great treat for myself.

We went here three times during our three night stay at Bally's Hotel. Very conveniently located at Grand Bazaar Shops downstairs.

Tried: The Mutt Dog, The Green Dog, Elote Dog, The House Dog

I would definitely recommend The Mutt Dog which is basically The Green Dog with a little spicy kick.

The workers mistakingly gave away one of our hot dogs so the manager hooked it up with a free House Dog on the house (No Pun Intended). Would definitely be back!

This place is amazing. I was hungry for a quick snack after gettig toasted at the fuel bar. The service was good but it would have been better if they would've had tacos or more fryers available. Still I would give my highest of recommendations to this place. It's great. I grew up with am elotero an he's hard to find these days. This is the spot. So come and check it out. Joanna came by to check in us and we have her our feedback. She was super nice. I ove Las Vegas so I will recommend anything that supports our hometown. Please check it out. Hope you enjoy...

I saw this place on yelp while looking for aces to eat and I knew I had to try it out! The cashier/cook was super helpful and explained each item they had on their menu and was really friendly! Prices weren't too crazy for the strip and the dogs came out quick! I ate the red dog which was offered a nice kick of spice with the chipotle aioli and spicy tomato sauce! The onions were cooked to perfection and offered great texture! The hotdog itself was huge and tasty! I also tried deep fried oreos for the first time here and with the horchata cream, these were so bomb! Super soft and on the inside and warm with a crunchy outside! I would definitely recommend this place to anyone who loves gourmet hotdogs!

I really Iike this place!  I came here during my break at work a couple of times.  I've never been to the one in LA, but I was told that I definitely had to give it a shot.  

The chili dog here is among the best I've had, and definitely the best I've had in Vegas.  The fry combinations with sauces are amazing as well, and I've been back several times to try them all.  If you're walking the strip and have a craving for a street hot dog, this is definitely the place to go!

Very good hot dog quality with some slightly weird flavor profile decisions. 

I ordered both the Elote and the House dog. I felt both were slightly odd flavor/texture choices. However, the bun was "lobster roll" style, which I guess just means it was buttered. This was quite decadent, in its savoriness. 

The hot dog is large and of high quality. It tastes of pure beef and fat. It holds a solid bite. 

The Elote dog is covered with corn, parmesan cheese, and some endless panoply of other toppings. 

My advice would be to stick to the most basic dog you can find here. The toppings just sort of distracted from the nice hot dog.
This place is "OFF THE CHAIN!!!!!" 1st time to Las Vegas & we couldn't have found a better lunch spot!!!!!! The staff is extremely friendly as well!!!!!

Dirt Dog was just one of the very few highlights on the Vegas Strip. It's tucked away in a small shopping area close to Alex and Ani, across from a huge Vegas souvenir store. It's on the east side of the strip, south of the Linq. When we arrived, there was only one guy working. It took awhile for the 6 of us to get our dogs because they are pretty complex hot dogs.

It was worth the wait. I ordered the red dog. It was the perfect level of spicy. The bacon wrapped dog was excellent. (They are all wrapped in bacon.) the bun was different, toasted, and freaking amazing. I also tried the elote, Mexican street corn. It was delicious, but super messy. I didn't see the photo of the corn in a cup until after I got corn all over my face. I would recommend asking for that if you want to stay cute.

Not bad at all. Very impressed with the flavor combination. 
I love LA street food and hot dogs and elotes are on the top of the list. 
I tried the elote dog and it didn't disappoint. 
The bun is not a normal hot dog bun. But since they put a lot of stuff on it. It needs to be out of the norm bun. 
I can't wait till they have more spots in town. 
This location is on the bazaar shops by the famous wahlberg burger spot.

My boyfriend won't shut up about how fabulous the hot dogs were- the house dog was our favorite! It was sweet, spicy and just gd delicious. Service was quick and "staff"- one person- was friendly and entertaining! It's a little hard to find though all the way in the back- but totally worth getting lost for!

Best damn hot dog around! I'm from California and I will be driving 2 hours to the LA area to have this hot dog again! The customer Service is amazing. Kenny, Allen, teddy and Kio delivered!  We will be back to this location the next time we're in Las Vegas!

This is a hidden gem in the Grand Bazaar Shops! It's around the corner from Wahlburgers and Fuel. The chef is very friendly and personable. The prices are decent for the amount of food you will be getting. 

We ordered the original dirt dog, the mutt dog, and elotes in a cup. All the hotdogs comes wrapped with bacon, which is the best thing that could ever happen to hotdogs! The buns they use are the England buns usually found with lobster rolls. It is perfectly buttered and toasted with a crunch on the outside and soft, warmth on the inside. 
The original dog is pretty much the basics of what would be in a hot dog (mustard, ketchup) with sautéed onions and green peppers. 
The mutt dog is a mix between the red dog and green dog, and boy is it spicy! Be prepared to have your mouth set on fire. 
The elotes were pretty good, it could have a bit too much of cheese, but all the right spices are there. 

I definitely would recommend this to all my friends and we are going to be returning here anytime we are in Vegas!

I wanted to make sure I stayed hungry for our dinner buffet, so I didn't want to order everything that I had wanted to try here, so I just got the Dirty Esquite, and boy, that was delicious.  My lime slice was a little dry, so I wish I had more lime juice for my elotes cup, but it was still good.  Definitely would order this again next time, along with a hot dog, some fries, and maybe the fried Oreos.

Dirt dog is located on the strip very close to Paris & Bally's. 
corn - could get it on or off the cobb. I got it off the cobb so it's not messy and was amazed at how flavorful it was. 
hot dog - friends had this and said it was super flavorful and tasty but pretty spicy so if you can't handle spice, stay away 
loaded fries - HUGE portion, friend had this and loved it

This place is the bombbbbbb!! Extra good, especially if you're buzzing and need something quick to eat. Gourmet! Flo is the man, great service to go along with great food. Definitely need to eat here if you're on the strip visiting or working.

Man this place is the bombbbbbbbbb diggaty I have never had a hot dog this good better then pinks for sure if you ever in vegas better try this especially if u like to pig out the cook was awesome as well food was awesome
Tucked away from everything and limited choices but fantastic. The Mexican street corner was fantastic and the chili dog was phenomenal. Must have!

I don't get why this is rated so high?  flavor wasn't bad, but @ $8 per dog - I won't be back

These are not hotdogs you can eat walking the strip, unless you want to wear most of it, and this location is just a stand really  - no seating except for benches and a tables in the outdoor mall - and you don't mind eating a hot dog on the 100+ degree sidewalk

someone in front of us ordered some nachos, so we saw the fry machine that they use, and how it failed to cook half of the chips as the employee stood there picking through what the machine dumped out

I was in Vegas and ate at several $$ and $$$ 4+ star restaurants and Dirt Dog was the best meal I had the whole trip. Do yourself a favor and grab a dog and a side here. I had the Elote Dog and Dirty Esquite corn side. Everything in the side dish was on my dog so next time I will change up my side. Regardless, everything was delicious! The staff was very friendly and even handed me a coupon for 2 for $10 craft beers at the bar next door to Dirt Dog. If six stars was an option, that's what I'd rate it.
Eeeh not bad, but not great. The pictures look really good, but the taste didn't reflect.

If you are looking for amazing food for a good price in Vegas, look no further. The loaded hot dogs here are incredible. It doesn't stop there -- the street corn and loaded fries are also awesome. I got whatever they recommended to me, but I wanted to try the whole menu. 

I've been to Vegas four times now and every time I've been disappointed with the food scene. The food tends to be expensive and mediocre at best. This was probably the cheapest and definitely the best meal I've had in Vegas.

Definitely a hot dog gone wild, but oh so good! One of the best hot dogs I have ever had! The elope fries were also extremely amazing and tastefully done! Go here now and your tastebuds will thank you!!

Great food! Great service! The cashier helped us with our decisions, explaining in detail what things were. He was also very friendly. The food looked good and tasted good. The cashier later came out and brought us a dessert he thought we would like, free of charge! Nice guy. Thanks again Dirt Dog Las Vegas!

We went here after reading the overwhelming positive reviews and were extremely disappointed by our visit. The food seemed old and smelled/tasted off which led to us getting sick. I would not recommend going here during your vacation.

Dirt Dog has hands down the best Dogs I've ever tasted. Kate and I left the Tao nightclub around 2 in the morning and stumbled across this GEM!! I ordered the House Dog and the Dirty Chili Dog. Katie ordered the Patti Melt Dog. These hotdogs were as gourmet as you can dress a dog. The buns were made from Texas toast. All the hotdogs get wrapped with bacon. Now I remind you we got these Hotdogs at night when this place was closing. Usually when it's later in the day or better yet your last orders you wouldn't expect things to taste all that fresh or good. But Kenny and his staff must love what they do. I honestly felt like the hotdog couldn't have been made any better. Kenny also was kind and generous and gave Kate and I dessert. This place wowed me, who knew you could make the hotdog this special. 

The House Dog: The hotdog is wrapped in bacon and has Thousand island and green chili spread. It's a heavy hotdog with tons of flavor. Honestly a little too much flavor for myself. It tastes good but was not my favorite from the ones I picked. 

The Dirty Dog: is every mans dream hotdog!! The classic chili cheese dog gourmet styled. I haven't tasted a good chili dog like that since I was a kid. This hotdog far exceeds the one I had as a kid to be honest. I wish I lived in Vegas just for this damn hotdog. 

The Patti Melt Dog: this hotdog came loaded with cheese and bacon and French fries. It also has an aioli spread that ties in perfect.   Katie said she wished she got one for the plane ride back home. 

Honestly wish the best for this establishment and hope they continue to succeed.

The customer service was AWESOME and the food was ON POINT. We had the house dog, dirty chili dog, elote and deep fried Oreos  Definite recommend if you're looking for a quick bite and good street food!
this small shop was singly manned this Wednesday afternoon (no waiting) but nevertheless my spicy mutt dog didn't disappoint.

Wow this place was incredible! I got the green dog which comes with chimichurrie and a bunch of other toppings. This was the best hot dog I've ever had in my life. Even the bun was toasted perfectly. Don't miss this place. I highly recommend.
The food tasted great and the service was great . Definitely coming back for more .you can taste the flavor that's on the hotdog's and the fries were the best to get .

Saw this place all over social media and had to plan a trip to try it. We got the Elote Dog & The House Dog! The Elote Dog was delicious, it is so huge so it's hard to get everything in one bite! Then bun is so soft and yummy. Basically I'd recommend this place! The price is decent for the size of the hot dog. The fries are also really good! There isn't much seating in this location so plan for that.

Hot dog hot dog hot diggity dog! This place was worth the find! I flew in from San Diego to try this place (literally) and it was worth it! I wish I took pictures but I ended up eating everything before realizing "oops! I should be taking artsy pics right now!"  I got the Green Dog and the Elote and both were SO GOOD. The customer service was excellent and I look forward to my next experience! #TheKingOfAllHotDogs #HappyBelly

Stopped by Dirt dog on a whim while walking the strip. Decided to try the cheesy corn, and WOW. It was super flavorful and filling! 

LaJunita was awesome and super knowledgeable about the food as well. My food was ready very quickly, and she even delivered it to me where I was sitting next door! Definitely recommend this spot to anyone who is looking for some good street style food!

This is the street food of Vegas! Surprisingly this was my best meal for my most recent visit! If you are looking for good cheap food then this is the place. Came here for lunch. The place is very small with limited seating outside. Everything on the menu sounded interesting. Wanted to order a dirty chili dog but the chili wasn't ready yet. I ended up with a green dog and my wife ordered a red dog. We also got a side of elote fries. Everything was delicious. I must say, it was probably the best hot dogs I've EVER had. 

Came back a second time before we left to try my dirty chili dog and my wife got the house dog. My chili dog was also delicious and one of the top chili dogs I've had but I enjoyed the green dog and my wife's red dog from the visit before more. I wasn't a huge fan of the house dog but it was still good. Luckily we ordered a mutt dog to share that was half red and half green for the last taste in my mouth. 

This will be my go to place for good cheap street food along side with Tacos El Gordo depending on what side of the strip in at.
This place sucks. They had no Mexican drinks like it said on their menu. All they had was gatorades and water. They had no tacos just hot dogs. So disappointed......

Visited this location while we were visiting Vegas and it was perfect for a late night meal after a few drinks!

There was only 1 person working to take orders and cook but it wasn't very busy and the food was worth the wait!

We got the House Dog and the Patty Melt Dog, both were out of this world!

I was starving after a long morning of travel & yelp recommended this spot! The "Mexican corn in a cup" is amazing! Staff is super nice! A must try! 

Slide over to Sin City next door and sit down to drink while Heather makes you a drink! You can eat your food there... Thank me later! Enjoy!

On 8/18 at about 7:45pm, I stop by Dirt Dog to grab a quick bite to go. Besides this location doesn't have a seating area! I waited about five minutes before the Cook told me the cashier would take my order shortly. Every order the cashier would open up the box and ask everyone did you order this (there was only about 4 customers) eventually my order came up (about 13 min) and he didnt even asked me, he just walk past to the other two customers and then into a restaurant eventually one of the employees standing outside had to go get him and tell him that it was my order. Not organized at all!!

Overall The House Dog is definitely better than their customer service. Very good snap on the dog lots of ingredients and all for under $4 dollars on the strip!!

Omg saw the rave on yelp and had to check it out and all I can say is it is delish! A must try if you are in Vegas. The place is located right in front of Bally's near this little area with different food stalls and mini shops. It is kinda hidden in the back so look carefully! My family ordered the dirty dog, elote dog, and the  dirty corn on a  stick. All of them were heaven in each bite. So buttery and flavorful. Highly recommend.

So bomb!! We ordered the red dog, the green dog, tinga fries, elote esquite, salt and pepper fries, and a beer. Everything was delicious. The staff is incredible!! The place is clean and fun. I truly enjoyed my experience here and as I local will be returning! Thank you.

First off, this place is tiny, it's in the Grand Bazaar shops (next to CVS/ Bally's entrance behind Wahburgers, hope that helps. I searched for a bit before I found it.

Now to the food..AMAZING!! Best dogs I think I have ever had. Buns are amazing, skin on the dogs snap when you bit them, all the ingredients taste fresh and work well together. Fries are good here also.

Service is great, very patient and willing to explain what is what. Listen to their history..pretty cool. Cook was amazing to watch.

Amazing food and very nice employee's!!! Definitely a spot you should check out if youre hungry and on the strip!!!

They even made me a special dog for my birthday!!! Awesome group of people and definitely know about customer service!
